\date{2026-05-15}
\title{Isomorphisms}
\author{fredrikbakke}
\meta{external}{https://github.com/samtoth/agda-synthetic-categories/pull/136}
\tag{changelog}
\import{stt-macros}

\subtree{
\title{Summary}

\p{
We formalise [isomorphisms](Synthetic.Categories.Isomorphisms) and finally
obtain a definition of [synthetic categories](Synthetic.Categories.Categories). Along
the way we formalise some useful definitions and lemmas.
}

\p{
Given two objects #{x} and #{y} in a type #{A}, we define an \em{isomorphism}
#{\Iso_A(x,y)} as a morphism #{f : \Hom_A(x,y)} together with two morphisms
#{s\ r : \Hom_A(y,x)} and two [triangles](Synthetic.Triangles)

\quiver{
\begin{tikzcd}
  y && y \\
	& x
	\arrow[equals, from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow["s", from=1-1, to=2-2]
	\arrow["f", from=2-2, to=1-3]
\end{tikzcd}
\quad
\begin{tikzcd}
  x && x \\
	& y
	\arrow[equals, from=1-1, to=1-3]
	\arrow["f", from=1-1, to=2-2]
	\arrow["r", from=2-2, to=1-3]
\end{tikzcd}
}
}

\p{
We show that in [Segal types](stt-00AI) [being an isomorphism is equivalent to
the postcomposition/precomposition map being an equivalence](fre-00OS), that being an
[isomorphism is a proposition](fre-00OT), and that
[isomorphisms are closed under composition and taking inverses](fre-00OU). To this
end we show that
[composition is associative in Segal types](Synthetic.Categories.AssociativitySegal).
}

\p{
We then define
[the walking isomorphism](Synthetic.Categories.WalkingIso) #{ℑ}, and show
that [it represents isomorphisms in Segal types](fre-00P0). A [category](fre-00OI) is
then a [precategory](stt-00GH) that is #{ℑ}-null, which as a condition
[is thus equivalent to the canonical map #{(x =_A y) \to \Iso_A(x,y)} being an
equivalence](fre-F900). En pessant we also define a [pregroupoid](fre-73B6) as a
precategory that is local at the inclusion #{\Delta^1 \to ℑ}.
}

\p{
Additionally, we formalise the basics of split morphisms and natural isomorphisms,
and formalise the definitions of [conservative maps](fre-00N4),
[essentially surjective maps](fre-2D88), [isofibrations](fre-A0N4).
}
}

